Regenerates the canonical tool-contracts documentation block in CLAUDE.md, template/CLAUDE.md, and README.md by querying the `--contract` output of six binaries (ctx-context, ctx-verify, ctx-scan, ctx-cage, ctx-brief, ctx-status), ensuring the docs cannot drift from the code. The single source of truth is the binary's own contract text.

Operates in two modes: `--write` (default) rewrites the marked block in place; `--check` (used by ctx-verify) emits `FAIL:` lines if any doc is stale. Requires all six binaries to already exist at `target/debug/` — the script never invokes cargo itself; install-tools.sh is the sole build step.

The marked region (between `<!-- BEGIN GENERATED tool-contracts ... -->` and `<!-- END GENERATED tool-contracts -->`) must exist in each doc file. In `--check` mode, a stale block causes a non-zero exit; in `--write` mode, any missing binary or marker causes immediate failure. Note: template/scripts/gen_tool_contracts.sh hardcodes `DOCS=(CLAUDE.md)` instead of mirroring this list, since scaffolded projects lack a template/ dir and document the cloned project, not the tooling itself.